        -:  156:/** \internal \returns the hyperbolic tan of \a a (coeff-wise)
        -:  157:    Doesn't do anything fancy, just a 13/6-degree rational interpolant which
        -:  158:    is accurate up to a couple of ulps in the (approximate) range [-8, 8],
        -:  159:    outside of which tanh(x) = +/-1 in single precision. The input is clamped
        -:  160:    to the range [-c, c]. The value c is chosen as the smallest value where
        -:  161:    the approximation evaluates to exactly 1. In the reange [-0.0004, 0.0004]
        -:  162:    the approximation tanh(x) ~= x is used for better accuracy as x tends to zero.
        -:  163:
        -:  164:    This implementation works on both scalars and packets.
